      <textAnnotation id="sid-7D890713-1638-4A47-94B0-7E62184016A7" signavio:alignment="left">
         <extensionElements>
            <signavio:signavioDictionaryLink propertyId="name">
               <signavio:dictionaryLink>/glossary/e9945c9938454c5d8c92e48e6ea45d1c</signavio:dictionaryLink>
            </signavio:signavioDictionaryLink>
            <signavio:signavioType dataObjectType="IT-System"/>
            <signavio:signavioMetaData metaKey="bgcolor" metaValue="#e1e1e1"/>
            <signavio:signavioMetaData metaKey="bordercolor" metaValue="#000000"/>
         </extensionElements>
         <text>IPAR</text>
      </textAnnotation>
      <textAnnotation id="sid-2DD531AF-FC83-4EC1-B604-C42E2354A0F8" signavio:alignment="left" textFormat="text/plain">
         <extensionElements>
            <signavio:signavioMetaData metaKey="bordercolor" metaValue="#000000"/>
         </extensionElements>
         <text>Must be able to able to expire pricing for product in RT Status. For NON IA products -The pricing tool expires the pricing products if the price was originally uploaded through the tool. For IA products (CPU, Chipsets, Wireless) and NON IA products that had price uploaded outside the tool (manually) or via My Deals tool, we run a report in Price.Intel.Com that identifies them so we can expire the price via manual template in SAP</text>
      </textAnnotation>
      <textAnnotation id="sid-EF37F8A7-8397-4337-A65E-AD31A325B75C" signavio:alignment="left" textFormat="text/plain">
         <extensionElements>
            <signavio:signavioMetaData metaKey="bordercolor" metaValue="#000000"/>
         </extensionElements>
         <text>1.Manual Upload takes place when the Boundary Apps are facing downtime.
2.Create, Change and expirations will be taking place
3.Allow create change if product is retired - only allow expire</text>
      </textAnnotation>
      <textAnnotation id="sid-8D06167E-AA1F-4F61-9BAB-0DA1DEFE917D" signavio:alignment="left">
         <extensionElements>
            <signavio:signavioDictionaryLink propertyId="name">
               <signavio:dictionaryLink>/glossary/019af034e6c44656a2363ee06d962907</signavio:dictionaryLink>
            </signavio:signavioDictionaryLink>
            <signavio:signavioType dataObjectType="IT-System"/>
            <signavio:signavioMetaData metaKey="bgcolor" metaValue="#e1e1e1"/>
            <signavio:signavioMetaData metaKey="bordercolor" metaValue="#000000"/>
         </extensionElements>
         <text>My Deals</text>
      </textAnnotation>
      <textAnnotation id="sid-01B4C3B1-F992-4264-90F7-5B9C9BFEA474" signavio:alignment="left" textFormat="text/plain">
         <extensionElements>
            <signavio:signavioMetaData metaKey="bordercolor" metaValue="#000000"/>
            <signavio:signavioLabel bold="true" fill="#ff0000" fontFamily="" fontSize="24.0" italic="" ref="text-left"/>
            <signavio:signavioLabel bold="true" fill="#ff0000" fontFamily="" fontSize="24.0" italic="" ref="text-right"/>
         </extensionElements>
         <text>Flow has been migrated to BIC. Please inform Process Steward:  Galceran, Nuria &lt;nuria.galceran@intel.com&gt;, and BPM Champion: Rebeca, Meza Redondo &lt;rebeca.meza.redondo@intel.com&gt; of any changes that occur within the flow from now onwards so that changes can be accurately reflected within BIC</text>
      </textAnnotation>
   </process>
